<subSubSection id="C305657F157F2A3CD5D4FB2A4A25FE9F" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="754" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA036F4157F2A3DD5D4FB2A4B7DFA39" blockId="26.[178,1086,1233,1451]" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Length 
<quantity id="4CE79B11157F2A3DD4BBFB294B65FB75" box="[477,592,1233,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.06" metricValueMax="7.12" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" unit="mm" value="7.06" valueMax="7.12" valueMin="7.0">7-7.12 mm</quantity>
. Body shiny, blackish-brown, abdomen reddish, posterior half of the male fourth free abdominal tergite and the whole fourth brown, antennae reddish, legs yellowish-red. Second antennomere shorter than the first, third longer than the second, fourth to tenth longer than wide. Eyes longer than the postocular region in dorsal view. Reticulation of the fore-body evident and fine. Reticulation of the abdomen absent. Puncturation of the head visible, but absent on a narrow longitudinal median band and on frons. Puncturation of the elytra evident and close, that of the abdomen fine. Aedeagus: 
<figureCitation id="13242A71157F2A3DD4DCFA6D4B7DFA39" box="[442,584,1429,1451]" captionStart="Figs 157-168" captionStartId="61.[178,218,1424,1444]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,220,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-2@61.[178,1085,220,1016]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figs 157-168: spermatheca, sixth free urotergum of female (158) and male (167), aedeagus in lateral and ventral view. (157-158): Lambanus rougemonti nov.gen., nov.sp.; (159-160): Drusilla sculpticollis PACE; (161): Drusilla bruneiorum PACE; (162-163): Drusilla divergens nov.sp.; (164- 168): Drusilla bulbosa nov.sp. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335497/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">Figs 162-163.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA036F4157F2A3DD5D4FA4148F7F9AD" blockId="26.[178,1085,1465,1599]" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s:Thenewspeciesissimilarto 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D77157F2A3DD65EFA424D38FA5D" authority="PACE, 2008" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2008" box="[824,1037,1465,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foeda">
<emphasis id="B96BEAE6157F2A3DD65EFA424AA5FA5D" box="[824,912,1465,1487]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">D. foeda</emphasis>
PACE, 2008
</taxonomicName>
also from Borneo. It differs in the lenghth/width ratio of the pronotum which is 0.93, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D77157F2A3DD5B6FA0A481EF995" box="[208,299,1521,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foeda">
<emphasis id="B96BEAE6157F2A3DD5B6FA0A481EF995" box="[208,299,1521,1543]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">D. foeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is 1.11, in the antennomeres four to eight which are longer than wide, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D77157F2A3DD441F9F6484AF9B1" box="[295,383,1549,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foeda">
<emphasis id="B96BEAE6157F2A3DD441F9F6484AF9B1" box="[295,383,1549,1571]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">D. foeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are transverse, and in the broad, truncate apex of the aedeagus, which in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D77157F2A3DD476F9D24852F9AD" box="[272,359,1577,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="753" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foeda">
<emphasis id="B96BEAE6157F2A3DD476F9D24852F9AD" box="[272,359,1577,1599]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="753">D. foeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA036F4157E2A3CD5D4FF234A25FE9F" blockId="27.[178,1085,218,270]" pageId="27" pageNumber="754">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet of the new species refers from the divergence of the characters of the aedeagus from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D77157E2A3CD710FF014A25FE9F" authority="PACE." authorityName="PACE." box="[630,784,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="754" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foeda">
<emphasis id="B96BEAE6157E2A3CD710FF014BF8FE9C" box="[630,717,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="754">D. foeda</emphasis>
PACE.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
